## Adyen Support Tickets

### When to open a ticket

- top-ups failing due to routing/intermediaries
- non-deterministic issues
- suspected scheme/network issues
- need Adyen rule/config change
- anything not explainable via UI

---

### Support link

https://help.adyen.com/knowledge/account/access-your-customer-area/how-do-i-reach-adyen-support

---

### What to include

**Always include “Issuing” in subject** (routing)

Include:
- Product (Issuing, etc.)
- Environment (TEST / LIVE)
- Payment Instrument ID
- Transfer ID
- Account Holder ID
- Balance Account ID
- Description of issue
- examples
- troubleshooting steps taken
- screenshots/videos (optional)

**Important:**
- Provide IDs in **text**, not just screenshots

---

### SLA

- First response: ~24 hours
- Resolution time varies

Depends on:
- issue complexity
- ticket quality
- completeness of data

> Better tickets = faster resolution

---

### Timing tip

Adyen uses follow-the-sun support:

- Late CET → US/APAC queues
- Non-urgent → send next CET morning

---

### Known issue

Rare but real:
- tickets can get “stuck” in queue

If no response in 1–2 business days:
- follow up
- escalate

